name: GET_DescribeNetworkInsightsAnalyses
description: Describes one or more of your network insights analyses.

NetworkInsightsAnalysisId.description: The ID of the network insights analyses. You must specify either analysis IDs or a path ID.

NetworkInsightsPathId.description: The ID of the path. You must specify either a path ID or analysis IDs.

AnalysisStartTime.description: The time when the network insights analyses started.

AnalysisEndTime.description: The time when the network insights analyses ended.

Filter.description:
The filters. The following are the possible values:

  • path-found - A Boolean value that indicates whether a feasible path is found.

  • status - The status of the analysis (running | succeeded | failed).

MaxResults.description: The maximum number of results to return with a single call. To retrieve the remaining results, make another call with the returned nextToken value.

DryRun.description: Checks whether you have the required permissions for the action, without actually making the request, and provides an error response. If you have the required permissions, the error response is DryRunOperation. Otherwise, it is UnauthorizedOperation.

NextToken.description: The token for the next page of results.

allOf.description: The name of the filter. Filter names are case-sensitive.

The filter values. Filter values are case-sensitive. If you specify multiple values for a filter, the values are joined with an OR, and the request returns all results that match any of the specified values.

Filter.description:
A filter name and value pair that is used to return a more specific list of results from a describe operation. Filters can be used to match a set of resources by specific criteria, such as tags, attributes, or IDs.

If you specify multiple filters, the filters are joined with an AND, and the request returns only results that match all of the specified filters.
